description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anaesthetic Department, Hammersmith Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Division of Surgery, Cardiovascular &amp; Cancer Division&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HAMMERSMITH HOSPITAL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Weds 3rd February &amp; Weds 4th August 2021 start&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 x post in either Cardiothoracic, Renal transplant or Hepatobiliary Anaesthesia&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are invited to apply for Trust Doctor Posts (ST5-7 Equivalent) in Anaesthesia, for the specialties Renal / Hepatobiliary / Cardiothoracic surgery. The successful candidates will be offered a mix of clinical training, and service in these specialist areas of anaesthesia. The successful candidates will be expected to work flexibly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Posts will commence &lt;strong&gt;as above&lt;/strong&gt; for a period of 6 months in the first instance, renewable up to 1 year depending on satisfactory performance, and the needs of the successful candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should have a minimum of 4 years anaesthetics experience and should also be registered with the GMC with a licence to practise, CCT desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FRCA or equivalent is essential and where equivalent qualifications or experience are being offered, it is essential the candidate provides written confirmation of this from the Royal College of Anaesthetists and attaches this confirmation to the application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants who do not provide this confirmation will not be put forward for short-listing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No late applications will be accepted.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews: 4th December (via Microsoft teams)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aiming to promote equal opportunities and a smoke free environment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Claire Boynton - claire.boynton3@nhs.net &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Ester Avagliano - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;esther.avagliano@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
